  <p class="footnotetext"><a href="#_ednref1" name="_edn1" class="fn" id="_edn1">[i]</a> Pursuant to Louisiana Supreme
  Court Rule XIX, Section 11E(3), since Respondent failed to answer the formal charges, the charges were deemed
  admitted and proven by clear and convincing evidence.</p>

  <p class="footnotetext"><a href="#_ednref2" name="_edn2" class="fn" id="_edn2">[ii]</a> Rule 1.4 provides in
  part:</p>

  <blockquote>
    <p class="footnotetext">"(a)  A lawyer shall keep a client reasonably informed about the status of a matter and
    promptlycomply with requests for information."</p>
  </blockquote>

  <p class="footnotetext">Rule 1.16  provides in part:</p>

  <blockquote>
    <p class="footnotetext">"(d) Upon termination of representation, a lawyer shall take steps to the extent reasonably
    practicable to protect a client's interests, such as giving reasonable notice to the client, allowing time for
    employment of other counsel, surrendering papers and property to which the client entitled and refunding any
    advance payment of fee that has not been earned.  The lawyer may retain papers relating to the client to the extent
    permitted by other law."</p>
  </blockquote>

  <p class="footnotetext"><a href="#_ednref3" name="_edn3" class="fn" id="_edn3">[iii]</a>  A review of the Orleans
  Parish Civil District Court record of the succession proceeding, which was submitted as an exhibit to the ODC's
  Deemed Admitted Submission on Sanctions, shows that Respondent appears to have filed this answer and reconventional
  demand in response to the "Petition to Be Appointed Administratrix, For Rule to Show Cause, For Temporary Restraining
  Order and for Preliminary and Permanent Injunctions" which had been filed by Ms. Polk's heirs in November of 1989. 
  The answer and reconventional demand does not appear to have been filed in response to the petition for possession
  which was filed in May of 1992 as asserted in the formal charges.  This information is pointed out for purposes of
  clarification only.</p>

  <p class="hiddenblock"><span class="allegedrules">1.16(d)</span></p>
